Let's dock the 373 fragment and top three inhibitors.

In [85]:
!obabel -ipdb ../data/UsingSmina/373ligand_only.pdb -omol2 -O _373.mol2
prot = Dock.protein('protein_minus_ligand.fixed.pdb', fix_pdb=True)
affinity = prot.score('ligand.mol2', output_sdf_file='_373.sdf')
print("Affinity of cystal pose of fragment 373:", affinity)

outputs = []
ligands = [754,742, 786]
ligand_sdf_files = []
for ligand in ligands:
    smiles = osa_mols.loc[f"OSA_000{ligand}"].SMILES_parent
    sdf_file = f'{ligand}.sdf'
    output = prot.dock(smiles, 
                       output_sdf_file=sdf_file,
                       autobox_ligand='_373.mol2', 
                       exhaustiveness=64, num_modes=1)
    output['lig_id'] = ligand
    output['sdf_file'] = sdf_file
    outputs.append(output)
    ligand_sdf_files.append(sdf_file)
    
outputs = pd.concat(outputs)

Aside from a bunch of hydrophobic interactions, the most interesting is definitely the pi stacking to the fluorobenzene in the 373 fragment. We should ensure all hits have this interaction, it'll help constrain hits to bind to the same pocket.
